[thinking] **Evaluating project structure for tests**
[thinking] 
[thinking] I’m considering that the project might only include src/test/java. The rule could be strict, but it seems support classes are acceptable. Another thought is to create source files under src/test/resources, but that doesn't appear to work. I might need to create separate Java source files with one public class per package/file, totaling around seven files. This could broaden the scope of the patch while still focusing on emulating missing legacy optional processor dependencies. I wonder if we need to reflect the configuration for these.
